    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen building in `ReleaseSafe` mode with Zig, there is a crash when the viewport\nscrolls down (e.g. when scrolling down in a file that is longer than 1 page).\n\nThis does not happen in any other optimize modes (`Debug`, `ReleaseFast`, `ReleaseSmall`).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Create a file that has more lines than your terminal does\n2. `zig build -Doptimize=ReleaseSafe run_dev -- --clean long_file.txt`\n3. Press `G` to go to the bottom of the file\n\n~~I could not figure out how to get a stacktrace :(~~ (WSL is dumb sometimes. There is a stack trace in the comments)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim shouldn't crash :)\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.0-dev (commit a15bf9c90a)\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 43 (WSL), Fedora 43 (bare-metal), Windows 11 (10.0.26200 Build 26200)\n\nAll are x86_64.\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWindows Terminal 1.23.13503.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nBuilt from source (Zig)",
