            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Adding `-fno-sanitize=undefined` to the flags seems to \"fix\" it:\n\n```diff\n--- a/build.zig\n+++ b/build.zig\n@@ -355,6 +355,7 @@ pub fn build(b: *std.Build) !void {\n         \"-std=gnu99\",\n         \"-DZIG_BUILD\",\n         \"-D_GNU_SOURCE\",\n+        \"-fno-sanitize=undefined\",\n         if (support_unittests) \"-DUNIT_TESTING\" else \"\",\n         if (use_luajit) \"\" else \"-DNVIM_VENDOR_BIT\",\n         if (is_windows) \"-DMSWIN\" else \"\",\n```\n\nI think this means that UBSan is catching undefined behavior and crashing because of it. Although, I am not sure why it is not catching it in `Debug` mode.",
