            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Thought I could fix it with #37172, but apparently it breaks some of the unit tests because the allocations are larger than expected; I'm also not sure how it affects the memory footprint. Perhaps disabling the ubsan would be better.\n\nThe issue was in an allocation, and it only occurs when the size of the allocation is known at compile time to be less than the size of the struct (because the struct includes padding for alignment). I put a small reproduction in the PR.",
