        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I found the specific UBSan option that's causing the crash. You can disable it (without disabling all UBSan) with the below patch:\n```diff\ndiff --git a/build.zig b/build.zig\nindex 26db0c66b6..fd539b4b02 100644\n--- a/build.zig\n+++ b/build.zig\n@@ -349,6 +349,7 @@ pub fn build(b: *std.Build) !void {\n         \"-std=gnu99\",\n         \"-DZIG_BUILD\",\n         \"-D_GNU_SOURCE\",\n+        \"-fno-sanitize=object-size\",\n         if (support_unittests) \"-DUNIT_TESTING\" else \"\",\n         if (use_luajit) \"\" else \"-DNVIM_VENDOR_BIT\",\n         if (is_windows) \"-DMSWIN\" else \"\",\n```\nFor more details, see [here](https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc-6.3.0/gcc/Instrumentation-Options.html).",
            "created_at": "2025-12-31T14:59:30Z",
