            "body": "@kylesower I created the repro you had in your PR, and [uploaded it to a Gist](https://gist.github.com/eamonburns/abcdc76fc9f97994939b87d550937f45) (with a couple modifications. i.e. add a `disable_check` option, and print \"(success)\" at the end of the `create_struct` function).\n\nI also created [a post on ziggit.dev](https://ziggit.dev/t/crash-due-to-ubsan-in-releasesafe-but-not-debug/13741?u=eamonburns) (a Zig help forum) asking why it crashes in `ReleaseSafe` but not `Debug`. (Edit: Looks like it is a problem with LLVM, and it is probably not fixable. Probably related to the warning below: \"clang: warning: the object size sanitizer has no effect at -O0, but is explicitly enabled: -fsanitize=object-size [-Winvalid-command-line-argument]\")",
