        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I don't think CMake enables sanitization by default. I checked `CONTRIBUTING.md` and found a way you can enable it, though:\n```\nrm -rf build && CMAKE_EXTRA_FLAGS=\"-DCMAKE_C_COMPILER=clang -DENABLE_ASAN_UBSAN=1\" make\n```\nI tried this and couldn't reproduce the same crash (though it does exit with code 1 when I simply open nvim and quit).",
